@node line "Music Line Editor"

@{b}MUSIC LINE EDITOR@{ub}
--------------------------

Po  "ART  OF  NOISE"  przyszedî  czas na nastëpny scenowy edytor muzyczny.
Musicline  Editor  jest  programem  8  kanaîowym.   Posiada dodatkowo duűo
efektów  specjalnych.   Ma  jednak  doôę  duűe  wymagania.   Po pierwszych
testach  mogë stwierdzię, űe jednak ustëpuje programowi Art of Noise.  Czy
przyjmie sië na scenie - zobaczymy.  Jak zwykle wszystko zaleűy od Was.

Wymagania: OS 2.x/3.x

Hardware: A1200, najlepiej z Fastem i lepszym procesorem

Program:
 
  4/8 channels
  5 octaves
  1024 parts
  128 steps maximum part length (flexible)
  256 sequencer steps
  255 instruments
  255 wavesamples
  Separate sequencelist for each channel
  Realtime part transpose
  Separate speed/groove in each channel
  127kb maximum sample-size
  5 effects per notestep
  256 subtunes per module
  Flexible instrument structure:
   Each wavesample can be used in multiple instruments
   16/32/64/128/256 bytes waveform length for realtime effects
   Volume
   Semitone
   Finetune
   Auto glide
   Transposable on/off
   Envelope (ADSR; Attack, Decay, Sustain, Release)
   Vibrato
   Tremolo
   Arpeggio (with multiple subeffects)
   Realtime waveform effects:
    Transform
    Phasing
    Mix (can be used as a Chorus)
    Resonance
    Filter (resonance & normal)
   Animation (create a sample of your synthetic sound)
   Playloop (put realtime effects on samples, like
   phasing & timestretch etc.)
   Sample start & end offset
   Loop (multiple directions)
   Protracker module loading compatible


Struktura zapisu
-----------------
 
 Part Data

    00  --- 00 00xy 0000 0000 0000 0000
      \    \  \  \ \
       \    \  \  \ Effect Parameter
        \    \  \  Effect Number
         \    \  Instrument
	  \    Note
	   Position


Lista efektów
--------------

  0x   Pitch

  01xx SlideUp              : speed
  02xx SlideDown            : speed
  03xx Glide                : speed
  04xx InitInstrumentGlide  : 00
  05xx PitchAdd             : add xx to pitch
  06xx PitchSub             : sub xx from pitch
  07xx VibratoSpeed         : speed
  08xx VibratoUp            : depth 00-40
  09xx VibratoDown          : depth 00-40
  0Axx VibratoWave          : 00 - sine
                              01 - rampdown
                              02 - sawtooth
                              03 - square
  0Bxx SetFineTune          : E1-1F


  1x   Instrument Volume

  10xx SetVolume            : volume 00-40
  11xx VolumeSlideUp        : speed
  12xx VolumeSlideDown      : speed
  13xx SetSlideToVolume     : volume 00-40
  14xx SlideToVolume        : speed
  15xx VolumeAdd            : add xx to volume 00-40
  16xx VolumeSub            : sub xx from volume 00-40
  17xx TremoloSpeed         : speed
  18xx TremoloUp            : depth 00-40
  19xx TremoloDown          : depth 00-40
  1Axx TremoloWave          : 00 - sine
                              01 - rampdown
                              02 - sawtooth
                              03 - square


  2x   Channel Volume

  20xx SetVolume            : volume 00-40
  21xx VolumeSlideUp        : speed
  22xx VolumeSlideDown      : speed
  23xx SetSlideToVolume     : volume 00-40
  24xx SlideToVolume        : speed
  25xx VolumeAdd            : add xx to volume 00-40
  26xx VolumeSub            : sub xx from volume 00-40
  27xx SetVolumeAllChannels : volume 00-40


  3x   Master Volume

  30xx SetVolume            : volume 00-40
  31xx VolumeSlideUp        : speed
  32xx VolumeSlideDown      : speed
  33xx SetSlideToVolume     : volume 00-40
  34xx SlideToVolume        : speed
  35xx VolumeAdd            : add xx to volume 00-40
  36xx VolumeSub            : sub xx from volume 00-40


  4x   Other

  40xx SpeedOneChannel      : speed 00-1F
  41xx GrooveOneChannel     : speed 00-1F
  42xx SpeedAllChannels     : speed 00-1F / tempo 20-FF
  43xx GrooveAllChannels    : speed 00-1F
  44xx ArpeggioList         : number
  45xx ArpeggioListOneStep  : number
  46xx Sustain              : 00 - release / 01 - hold
  47xx Filter               : 00 - off / 01 - on
  48xx SampleOffset         : offset (ex. 32=3200)
  49xx RestartNoVolume      : 00
  4Axx WaveSample           : number
  4Bxx InitInstrument       : 00


  Ex   ProTracker

  E1xx SlideUp              : speed
  E2xx SlideDown            : speed
  E3xx Portamento           : speed
  E40x FineSlideUp          : value
  E50x FineSlideDown        : value
  E6xx VolumeSlideUp        : speed
  E7xx VolumeSlideDown      : speed
  E8xy Tremolo              : x - speed / y - depth
  E90x TremoloWave          : 00 - sine
                            : 01 - rampdown
                            : 02 - square
  EAxy Vibrato              : x - speed / y - depth
  EBxx VibratoWave          : 00 - sine
                              01 - rampdown
                              02 - square


 Arpeggio Effect Commands

  1xx SlideUp               : speed
  2xx SlideDown             : speed
  3xx SetVolume             : volume 00-40
  4xx VolumeSlideUp         : speed
  5xx VolumeSlideDown       : speed
  6xx Restart               : 00


@endnode
