@node c64 "C64 wiecznie űywy"

@{b}FRODO@{ub}
--------------

Jest juű kolejna wersja emulatora programowego C64.  Niestety nie posiadam
oryginalnego  Romu  C64,  wiëc  nici  z  odpalania.  Autorem programu jest
twórca super przeboju - Shape Shiftera (emulator Maca).

Irek P/UNN

@endnode

@node real "Real 3D 3"

@{b}REAL 3D v3@{ub}
-------------------

Juű  jest  najnowszy  pakiet  do raytracingu. A oto list nowych funkcji:

 - Triset  meshes allow colorization of individual faces -> better
   support for converted triangle objects
 - New normal orientation feature to fix phong shading problems of
   converted objects (Modify/freeform/Surface type)
 - General  polygonal  conversion  enables  more  complete  object
   export
 - Backdrop image is visible through clip mapped surfaces
 - Settings/attributes allows definition of default depth and name
   of objects
 - Repeat last action feature with a hot key
 - Edit   primitive  geometry  for  accurate  numeric  editing  of
   primitives
 - Automatic   field   Interlacing  feature  for  field  to  frame
   conversion
 - Interactive  hierarchical  skeletons with better IK control and
   angle constraints
 - Improved  Inverse  Kinematics method accepts multiple parameter
   curves and snaps automatically to the nearest joint
 - Draw as bounding box - object attribute
 - Fast background image drawing function
 - New  window  type,  toolbar, which includes useful creation and
   modelling

    features such as:

 - Coordinate input
 - Creation depth input by value and by a user defined line
 - Angle input for rotations
 - Important  hot-key  functions like Tab=Center Del=Undo-one-step
   etc.  available as buttons for easier 'getting started'
 - New 'key frame' animation method:
 - Saves   memory,   because  key  positions  are  represented  as
   coordinate systems
 - Does  not  generate  unintentional  elastic stretches on target
   objects
 - Shrink  wrap  available  as an animation method A new 'Surface'
   method,   which   makes   rotating,   walking   etc.    objects
   automatically move along surfaces

    Much improved key editor:

 - Anim playback control
 - Integrated  interface  for  creating and editing most animation
   methods
 - New key creation and deletion control
 - 'Redistribute evenly' function
 - Envelope control for accurate key frame animation editing
 - Discrete morphing for immediate shape changes
 - Complete  tag  morphing  support  can be used to e.g.  dissolve
   objects by morphing the new fade property
 - Curve  knot  timing of path based methods is now possible 8 bit
   alpha channel output in IFF file rendering
 - Non-adaptive,  super  sampled  rendering for best anti-aliasing
   quality
 - Open post-processing interface for various special effects like
   lens flares, global fogs etc.  The interface allows third party
   developers to hook post-effect libraries to Real 3D
 - New  'fade'  object  attribute,  which enables easy fade-in and
   fade-out of objects, quickly rendered transparent layers etc.
 - 'Glow'  material  property  for  creating  coronas, fire, laser
   beams  etc.  New material color handler for defining a constant
   material color which replaces object's original color.
 - New  'Roughness.   mathematical bump map, with density and bump
   height control
 - New  'Dither'  mathematical  color  map  with  density and bump
   height control
 - Additional  Edge  X/Y  gradient  control  for texture gradients
   allows  sharp  texture  map edges with interpolated texture map
   interior
 - Infinite  tiling  is  now  possible  also when applying FreqX/Y
   feature  to make texture Denser - this fixes the 'seam' problem
   in spherical mapping.
 - Much faster clip mapping
 - Round  modify  function  for  easy  edge  rounding  of  curves,
   polygons etc.
 - Primitives   can  now  been  edited  using  accurate  numerical
   Interface
 - RPL  has  been extended much, especially GUI programming is now
   possible.
 - Camera  view  mode  windows  are  now  updated instantly when a
   camera  object  has  been  modified,  not only during animation
   play.
 - Improved FLI/FLC support
 - A  feature  to  project  mouse coordinates to existing objects:
   this  enables  e.g.  drawing a curve directly on the surface of
   another object.
 - Modify/Special/Reflect  feature  makes  it  possible to place a
  highlight  from a light source to a location pointed by a mouse
  click.
 - Special/Vectors/Deselect   Group   can   be   used  to  exclude
   overlapping points when creating sub groups
 - Fractal generator (Tree/Landscape) parameter loading and saving
 - A  new  animation  method  attribute to torn off Inheritance of
   time modifications
 - Plug-in support for post-processing effects (i.e.  lens flares)
 - Essence  textures  will  implemented  via an external "plug-in"
   called  Realize!  (which will also include such effects as lens
   flares)
 - Numeric input for many tools
 - Background images to align objects
 - Constraints for object joints.
 - Much faster (up to 5 times in some cases) B-Spline rendering
 - Better DXF format object conversion
 - rewritten clip mapping
 - Interactive hierarchical skeletons
 - Skeletal  constrains,  min/max  angles  of  rotations,  2D & 3D
   joints
 - IFF file in the background
 - Shrink Wrap animation method
 - Much better TRUE keyframing
 - Along surface animation method
 - Envelopes
 - Open  post-processing  interface  for special effects like fog,
   lens flare
 - Object fading
 - "glow" parameter in material editor
 - New antialiasing
 - "Round" function in modelling
 - full GUI addition to RPL
 - Camera view are updated constantly
 - New animation methods.

lista poprawionych bîëdów:
 
 - Saving/reloading links no longer makes links 'read-only'
 - Box  rendering  to  a file uses now box dimensions as it should
   (this bug was only In Windows version)
 - Deleting/adding  points  from/to multiple freeform objects work
   correctly now.
 - Field rendering bug fixed (odd fields were shifted up!)
 - Boolean rethink bug of cut pyramid fixed
 - Ellipsegment  wireframe  problems  fixed  (Lathe tool sometimes
   produced invalid wireframes, which could not be recreated after
   reloading)
 - Invisible  compound objects are invisible in modifications also
   after saving and reloading.
 - The  font curve extractor creates only spline curves Previously
   some  characters  of  certain fonts produced polygonal outlines
   that could not be extruded (Windows version)
 - Font curve extractor/Scandinavia character map bug fixed
 - Box  rendering sometimes created errors on the right and bottom
   edge of the box This is now fixed
 - Anti-aliasing  to  backdrop  image  works  now properly also in
   Amiga version
 - Backdrop image is now visible through clip mapped surfaces
 - Parallel   curve   for   polygonal   lines   works  better  now
   Modify/Freeform/Distribute works now properly also with complex
   curves with over 200 points
 - Environment  rendering  set  environment gradient automatically
   This does not happen any more.

@endnode

